variable - valid promotion
double - None
float - double
long - float or double
int - double, float or long
char - int, long, float, double
short - int, long, float, double (but not char)
byte - short, int, long, float, double (but not char)

#we can't promote an argument from highly level to lower one, like from double to int
#sometimes it's required to explicitly cast(converts) double values to "temporarly" integer
	square((int) double_value) // explicitly converting the double value to integer